# Flutter Map Configurations

# To configure and run the Flutter customer app with Mapbox or Google Maps,
# use `--dart-define` or `--dart-define-from-file` to pass these variables:

# Option A: Mapbox Tiles (Recommended for dark theme mapping)
# MAPBOX_ACCESS_TOKEN=pk.your_mapbox_public_token

# Option B: Google Maps Tiles (Needs a Google Maps API Key)
# GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=AIzaSyYourKeyHere

# Examples:
# 1. Run with Mapbox:
#    flutter run --dart-define=MAPBOX_ACCESS_TOKEN=pk.your_mapbox_public_token
#
# 2. Run with Google Maps:
#    flutter run --dart-define=GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=AIzaSyYourKeyHere
#
# 3. Build release APK with Mapbox:
#    flutter build apk --dart-define=MAPBOX_ACCESS_TOKEN=pk.your_mapbox_public_token
#
# Note: If no environment variables are supplied, the app automatically falls back
# to CartoDB Dark Matter tiles, which are completely free and require no keys.
